Nairobi county tops the list of the most vaccinated counties with 34.7 per cent of its population having taken the jab. It is followed closely by Nyeri county which has 32.2 per cent. Laikipia County is third with 25.6 per cent followed by Kiambu with 22.9 per cent. On the other hand, pastoralists communities top the list of counties that have recorded low numbers of those vaccinated against Covid-19. Tana River has the least number at 3.6 per cent followed by Turkana with 4.4 per cent. Wajir is third with 4.6 per cent.